ðŸ“˜ DDL (Data Definition Language)
DDL is used to define and manage database objects like tables, schemas, indexes.
Common Commands
CREATE â†’ Create new database objects
ALTER â†’ Modify existing objects
DROP â†’ Delete objects

Example Structure
sql
-- Create a table
CREATE TABLE Students (
    StudentID INT PRIMARY KEY,
    Name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
    Department VARCHAR(50),
    Email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE
);
-- Alter table (add a new column)
ALTER TABLE Students
ADD DateOfBirth DATE;

-- Drop table
DROP TABLE Students;



ðŸ“˜ DML (Data Manipulation Language)
DML is used to manipulate data inside tables.

Common Commands
INSERT â†’ Add new rows
UPDATE â†’ Modify existing rows
DELETE â†’ Remove rows
SELECT â†’ Retrieve data

Example Structure
sql
-- Insert data
INSERT INTO Students (StudentID, Name, Department, Email)
VALUES (1, 'Subham', 'Computer Science', 'subham@example.com');

-- Update data
UPDATE Students
SET Department = 'Information Technology'
WHERE StudentID = 1;

-- Delete data
DELETE FROM Students
WHERE StudentID = 1;

-- Select data
SELECT StudentID, Name, Department, Email
FROM Students;
